  "prompt": "Is UT Austin a good school?",
  "response": "Yes, the University of Texas at Austin (UT Austin) is widely regarded as a **top-tier public research university** and is consistently ranked among the best public universities in the United States. Here are some reasons why UT Austin is considered a good school:\n\n### **Academic Excellence**\n- Ranked #1 among public universities in Texas and #9 among national public universities by *U.S. News & World Report (2024)*.\n- Highly regarded programs in **business (McCombs School of Business)**, **engineering (Cockrell School of Engineering)**, **computer science**, **natural sciences**, and **liberal arts**.\n- Renowned faculty, including Nobel laureates and members of prestigious academies.\n\n### **Research and Innovation**\n- A leading research institution with over **$700 million** in annual research expenditures.\n- Home to cutting-edge facilities and centers, such as the Texas Advanced Computing Center (TACC) and the Dell Medical School.\n\n### **Student Life and Campus**\n- A vibrant campus culture with over **1,300 student organizations** and a strong sense of school spirit (Hook 'em Horns!).\n- Located in **Austin, Texas**, a dynamic city known for its music, tech industry, and cultural scene.\n\n### **Diversity and Global Impact**\n- A diverse student body with students from all 50 states and over 120 countries.\n- Strong alumni network, including notable figures like Michael Dell (founder of Dell Technologies) and Matthew McConaughey (Academy Award-winning actor).\n\n### **Affordability and Value**\n- As a public university, UT Austin offers a **strong academic experience** at a lower cost compared to many private institutions.\n- Generous financial aid and scholarship opportunities for in-state and out-of-state students.\n\n### **Athletics and Traditions**\n- A powerhouse in **NCAA Division I athletics**, particularly in football, basketball, and baseball.\n- Rich traditions, including the iconic UT Tower and the Bevo mascot.\n\nWhile UT Austin is competitive and rigorous, it offers a well-rounded experience that prepares students for success in their careers and beyond. Whether UT Austin is the \"right\" school for you depends on your academic interests, career goals, and personal preferences.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
